713
01:08:23,895 --> 01:08:26,351
Now l know why this place
looked so familiar.

714
01:08:26,440 --> 01:08:29,643
Chief Inspector Dreyfus lives here.

715
01:08:32,946 --> 01:08:35,651
I think he has received a faint.

716
01:08:37,117 --> 01:08:40,237
Wake up, Chief Inspector. Wake up.

717
01:08:40,329 --> 01:08:42,654
Chief Inspector!

718
01:08:42,748 --> 01:08:46,497
Hello? Are you in there, Chief Inspector?

719
01:08:46,586 --> 01:08:48,210
Hello?

720
01:08:49,213 --> 01:08:50,756
There's no reply.

721
01:08:50,840 --> 01:08:54,790
It’s no use. I think we will
have to go to Hong Kong without him.

722
01:08:55,261 --> 01:08:56,637
- ''We''?
- Yes.

723
01:08:56,721 --> 01:09:02,475
- You, l and Cato, who will translate for us.
- Not me. I am not going to Hong Kong.

724
01:09:02,561 --> 01:09:06,261
- Douvier would shoot me on sight.
- Not if he doesn't recognise you.

725
01:09:06,356 --> 01:09:08,930
- And he won't.
- Why not?

726
01:09:10,110 --> 01:09:14,523
We will leave that up to the great Balls.

727
01:09:15,991 --> 01:09:18,115
''The great balls''?

728
01:09:19,245 --> 01:09:24,915
At your service! Please forgive
the condition of my establishment,

729
01:09:25,001 --> 01:09:29,912
<i>but as the inspector knows -
the chief inspector knows...</i>

730
01:09:30,006 --> 01:09:32,046
- Auguste!
- Argh!

731
01:09:32,133 --> 01:09:36,427
- I’m so sorry. I beg your pardon.
- But as the chief inspector knows,

732
01:09:36,513 --> 01:09:39,514
- we were bombed.
- It sounds like you still are.

733
01:09:39,600 --> 01:09:43,218
Almost all my collection
was either destroyed or damaged.

734
01:09:43,312 --> 01:09:47,179
Starting Monday, I have to have a fire sale.

735
01:09:47,274 --> 01:09:49,730
You could call it
''The Great Balls of Fire Sale''.

736
01:09:49,819 --> 01:09:52,107
A catchy suggestion!

737
01:09:53,572 --> 01:09:54,948
<i>(blows) Cunny!</i>

738
01:09:55,032 --> 01:09:57,108
<i>(grunting)</i>

739
01:10:02,457 --> 01:10:06,455
l can't tell you how good it is
to see that you are still alive.

740
01:10:06,544 --> 01:10:11,207
It has been my privilege to serve
the good inspector - the chief inspector -

741
01:10:11,299 --> 01:10:12,959
for all these many years.

742
01:10:13,051 --> 01:10:15,293
Thirteen, to be precise.

743
01:10:15,387 --> 01:10:19,800
And his reported demise
was a real blow to me.

744
01:10:19,892 --> 01:10:22,015
Something's coming.

745
01:10:22,102 --> 01:10:24,973
Yes! Yes, Cunny! You are not dreaming.

746
01:10:25,064 --> 01:10:28,896
Our friend, our customer, is alive!

747
01:10:28,985 --> 01:10:31,061
Hello, Cunny.

748
01:10:32,071 --> 01:10:35,191
Now, how can l serve you?

749
01:10:35,283 --> 01:10:39,115
- Well...
- Through wind and mud, snow and hail,

750
01:10:39,204 --> 01:10:42,158
whether long or short, dark or pale.

751
01:10:42,248 --> 01:10:45,665
Remember that when duty calls,

752
01:10:45,752 --> 01:10:47,544
you've got Balls.

753
01:10:47,629 --> 01:10:49,171
<i>(clap of thunder)</i>

754
01:10:51,800 --> 01:10:55,252
- l gotta sit down.
- Yes, of course. Cunny! Quick!

755
01:10:55,346 --> 01:10:57,753
Please, please! Come along.

756
01:10:57,848 --> 01:11:00,422
That's right. There you are. Sit.

757
01:11:00,518 --> 01:11:04,101
- Come, come, come. Sit, sit, sit.
- You're not serious?

758
01:11:04,188 --> 01:11:07,604
There has been no time
to get new furniture.

759
01:11:07,692 --> 01:11:11,690
Since the blast,
he's much more comfortable. Please, sit.

760
01:11:11,779 --> 01:11:15,943
As a matter of fact,
I’ve been sleeping on him.

761
01:11:17,577 --> 01:11:18,822
Chief Inspector?

762
01:11:18,912 --> 01:11:21,747
I am leaving for Hong Kong
first thing in the morning.

763
01:11:21,832 --> 01:11:23,540
Hong Kong?

764
01:11:23,625 --> 01:11:27,706
Do you think you could pick me up
some cheap coolie hats?

765
01:11:27,796 --> 01:11:31,462
My dear Auguste,
I need your best Hong Kong disguise.

766
01:11:31,550 --> 01:11:35,678
Also, l will need something
extra special in the Godfather line.

767
01:11:36,347 --> 01:11:38,755
Doctor, please. You must help me.

768
01:11:38,849 --> 01:11:43,179
Is Clouseau real,
or am I going mad again?

769
01:11:43,271 --> 01:11:46,854
- What do you think?
- What do I think? What can l think?

770
01:11:46,941 --> 01:11:52,316
lf that nincompoop is really alive,
and the things l heard are true,

771
01:11:52,405 --> 01:11:56,984
he'll probably be decorated for rounding
up the biggest drug ring in France,

772
01:11:57,077 --> 01:11:59,698
and I’ll be a laughing stock.

773
01:12:00,122 --> 01:12:03,455
That sounds reasonable.
What are you going to do?

774
01:12:04,376 --> 01:12:06,499
What choice do I have?

775
01:12:06,587 --> 01:12:12,590
I either commit myself and come back
to be locked up in here, or...

776
01:12:14,387 --> 01:12:16,794
I go to Hong Kong.

777
01:12:48,339 --> 01:12:51,708
- Listen, I don't think I can do this.
- Of course you can.

778
01:12:51,801 --> 01:12:54,588
Just think yellow and follow me.

779
01:13:26,462 --> 01:13:31,208
Mr and Mrs... Lo Kee.

780
01:13:31,301 --> 01:13:34,255
<i>- (clattering)
- (man) You stupid clumsy oaf!</i>

781
01:13:34,345 --> 01:13:38,011
What the hell do you think you're doing?
You've ruined my suit!

782
01:13:38,099 --> 01:13:41,765
Why the hell don't you
look where you're going?!

783
01:13:41,853 --> 01:13:45,851
I am Mr Algo. When Mr Scallini arrives,
have me paged in the bar.

784
01:13:45,941 --> 01:13:48,017
Certainly, Mr Algo.

785
01:13:49,320 --> 01:13:51,692
Who is gonna pay for my suit?

786
01:13:53,783 --> 01:13:58,492
See that man that was right there? That's
Guy Algo, Philippe's right-hand man.

787
01:13:58,579 --> 01:14:02,198
This Scallini must be
Mr Big from New York.

788
01:14:02,917 --> 01:14:05,455
Listen. We'll go up to the room.

789
01:14:05,545 --> 01:14:08,380
You stay here ten minutes,
then tell Mr, um...

790
01:14:08,465 --> 01:14:11,549
- Algo.
- Right. Yes, Algo. Yes.

791
01:14:11,635 --> 01:14:14,754
..Mr You-Know-Who has arrived,
and bring him to the room.

792
01:14:14,846 --> 01:14:19,224
- Mr You-Know-Who?
- l will be Mr You-Know-Who. Get it?

793
01:14:19,309 --> 01:14:21,136
Right. Come, Ming Loy.

794
01:15:03,981 --> 01:15:07,101
You got a reservation for Scallini.

795
01:15:12,657 --> 01:15:17,236
Page Mr Algo in the bar.
Tell him Mr Scallini's here.

796
01:15:39,769 --> 01:15:44,561
- What do you think you're doing?
- Mr Scallini in lobby.

797
01:17:01,938 --> 01:17:03,219
<i>Cochon.</i>

798
01:17:03,314 --> 01:17:05,391
<i>No, no. Fongu.</i>

799
01:17:17,955 --> 01:17:23,080
<i>Hey, you heard what l said to him?
Dumb Frenchman! ''Cochon''.</i>

800
01:17:23,169 --> 01:17:25,327
That means ''pig''.

801
01:17:26,005 --> 01:17:28,710
I tell Mr Scallini you're here.

802
01:17:37,392 --> 01:17:39,800
- Listen, boss!
- It’s not boss. It’s me.

803
01:17:39,894 --> 01:17:43,014
- Where is he?
- Getting into his Godfather disguise.

804
01:17:43,106 --> 01:17:46,890
Algo's in the next room.
Scallini's down the hall in the Tang suite.

805
01:17:46,985 --> 01:17:50,935
- We rode up in the same elevator.
- Maybe l can reach him before Philippe.

806
01:17:51,031 --> 01:17:55,076
- What will you do?
- I’m not sure. Keep your eye on Algo.

807
01:18:19,144 --> 01:18:20,555
<i>(spills drink)</i>

808
01:18:20,645 --> 01:18:22,722
- Ice?
- Please.

809
01:18:27,152 --> 01:18:29,228
- Soda?
- Yes.

810
01:18:34,535 --> 01:18:36,860
I hope it's not too strong.

811
01:18:36,954 --> 01:18:39,030
I’m sure it will be fine.

812
01:18:40,541 --> 01:18:43,293
Heh-heh-heh! Ha-ha-ha-ho!

813
01:18:44,087 --> 01:18:47,290
<i>Hey! Mamma mia! Ho-ho!</i>

814
01:18:47,382 --> 01:18:49,458
<i>Spaghettini to Al Pacino!</i>

815
01:18:49,551 --> 01:18:52,124
Heh-heh! Ho-ho!

816
01:18:52,220 --> 01:18:57,048
Carlo and me have got a little business
to talk over. We won't be long.

817
01:18:57,142 --> 01:19:00,677
Have another drink. Ho-ho-ho!

818
01:19:00,771 --> 01:19:03,344
<i>Viva Zapata! Ha-ha-ha!</i>

819
01:19:06,652 --> 01:19:08,395
- Where is she?
- I don't know.

820
01:19:08,487 --> 01:19:10,563
<i>(knocking)</i>

821
01:19:14,869 --> 01:19:16,945
<i>(mouths)</i>

822
01:19:17,622 --> 01:19:20,113
- Hello, Mr Marchione.
- Hey.

823
01:19:21,459 --> 01:19:23,867
- Come on in.
- Thank you. Thank you very much.

824
01:19:23,962 --> 01:19:27,580
- Can l get you a drink?
- Oh, no. Nothing, thank you.

825
01:19:27,674 --> 01:19:31,624
- It’s, uh... Simone.
- Oh, you really have a good memory.

826
01:19:31,720 --> 01:19:34,638
Well, I never forget a pretty face.

827
01:19:34,723 --> 01:19:37,345
Hey, boss. This is Simone.

828
01:19:37,434 --> 01:19:41,384
- That's Douvier's personal...
- Secretary. How do you do, Mr Scallini?

829
01:19:41,480 --> 01:19:46,356
We never met before.
lf we meet before, you call me Julio.

830
01:19:46,444 --> 01:19:50,228
- That's a nice hand.
- Thank you. That's only the right one.

831
01:19:50,323 --> 01:19:52,197
- You type too?
- 100 words a minute.

832
01:19:52,283 --> 01:19:54,110
l may faint.

833
01:19:54,202 --> 01:20:00,572
Mr Douvier is running a little late. lf you
like, I’ll keep you company till he arrives.

834
01:20:00,667 --> 01:20:03,372
lf l like? Does my mother cook spaghetti?

835
01:20:04,004 --> 01:20:06,376
<i>To the Gannet transaction.</i>

836
01:20:13,097 --> 01:20:15,967
Shall l tell Douvier we're on our way?

837
01:20:16,058 --> 01:20:18,051
<i>(choking)</i>

838
01:20:18,144 --> 01:20:20,717
Don't forget the money.

839
01:20:20,813 --> 01:20:22,640
<i>(coughs and splutters)</i>

840
01:20:30,448 --> 01:20:32,192
What?

841
01:20:32,283 --> 01:20:34,157
Throat?

842
01:20:34,244 --> 01:20:35,904
Back?

843
01:20:35,996 --> 01:20:37,704
Choking!

844
01:20:37,789 --> 01:20:41,372
You want me to hit you on the back?

845
01:20:41,460 --> 01:20:43,536
<i>(karate yell)</i>

846
01:21:01,981 --> 01:21:03,144
Aaagh!

847
01:21:03,232 --> 01:21:05,902
We're on our way.

848
01:21:05,985 --> 01:21:09,401
- Mr Douvier will meet us in the lobby.
- Great, great.

849
01:21:09,489 --> 01:21:11,861
- Is that it?
- Yep. Ha-ha-ha!

850
01:21:11,950 --> 01:21:15,236
- 50 million francs and no bodyguard?
- Listen, buddy.

851
01:21:15,328 --> 01:21:21,449
l take care of my body, my body takes
care of me. Know what I’m drivin' at?

852
01:21:28,592 --> 01:21:31,796
- I’ll buy you some cigarettes, huh?
- Smoke a few.

853
01:21:31,888 --> 01:21:36,680
When Douvier shows,
I’ll meet you in the lobby.

854
01:22:02,128 --> 01:22:03,788
<i>(fart)</i>

855
01:22:30,991 --> 01:22:33,280
Hey! Be right with you.

856
01:23:07,363 --> 01:23:09,604
What the hell is going on here?

857
01:23:26,883 --> 01:23:28,959
Lee Kee Shipyard.

858
01:23:35,684 --> 01:23:40,346
- Where'd he go?
- I think they went to Lee Kee Shipyard.

859
01:23:43,734 --> 01:23:45,109
Aaaargh!

860
01:24:00,460 --> 01:24:01,623
<i>(yells in Chinese)</i>

861
01:24:02,462 --> 01:24:05,878
See this? l can tell by your heart line
that you're very passionate.

862
01:24:05,966 --> 01:24:10,046
- See how long this is?
- Keep watchin'. It’s gonna get longer.

863
01:24:10,137 --> 01:24:12,010
<i>(phone)</i>

864
01:24:14,391 --> 01:24:17,096
<i>- Hello?
- Lee Kee Shipyard. Douvier.</i>

865
01:24:17,186 --> 01:24:19,344
It was Douvier.

866
01:24:19,438 --> 01:24:24,231
And the doorman heard him tell the driver
to go to the Lee Kee Shipyard.

867
01:24:24,318 --> 01:24:27,272
<i>Somethin' is cacuzza around here.</i>

868
01:24:29,282 --> 01:24:32,366
Your boss and a couple of boys
just left the hotel.

869
01:24:32,452 --> 01:24:37,743
- Really? I wonder why they did that.
- You got me. Why don't we go ask him?

870
01:24:38,249 --> 01:24:41,749
Yes. OK. Yes, I understand.

871
01:24:41,837 --> 01:24:43,379
OK. Yes.

872
01:24:44,423 --> 01:24:48,373
Douvier left the hotel about
five minutes ago. He was with two men.

873
01:24:48,468 --> 01:24:51,304
He told the driver
to go to the Lee Kee Shipyard.

874
01:24:51,388 --> 01:24:53,262
I’m sure it was that nincompoop!

875
01:24:58,771 --> 01:25:02,721
- I’m sure Mr Douvier won't be gone long.
- Well, we'll see.

876
01:25:02,817 --> 01:25:05,901
It doesn't make much sense
if you leave and he comes back.

877
01:25:05,987 --> 01:25:10,151
Stop worrying.
You'll give yourself wrinkles.

878
01:25:15,664 --> 01:25:20,789
- What about this Lee Kee Shipyard?
- Perfectly legitimate, as far as l know.

879
01:25:20,877 --> 01:25:23,914
They build a line
of expensive power cruisers.

880
01:25:24,006 --> 01:25:28,169
Maybe Mr Douvier
is just buying himself a yacht.

881
01:25:35,101 --> 01:25:38,351
<i>- Lee Kee Shipyard?
- That's what the come si chiama said.</i>

882
01:25:38,438 --> 01:25:40,726
<i>Come si chiama. Lee Kee.</i>

883
01:25:57,082 --> 01:25:58,826
Come on! Move it!

884
01:26:04,423 --> 01:26:06,001
Come on!

885
01:26:14,350 --> 01:26:16,426
<i>(sounds horn)</i>

886
01:26:40,085 --> 01:26:42,162
<i>(driver sounds horn)</i>

887
01:26:53,182 --> 01:26:55,259
<i>(horn)</i>

888
01:26:58,021 --> 01:27:00,097
<i>(siren)</i>

889
01:27:28,052 --> 01:27:30,128
Aaaargh!

890
01:27:53,954 --> 01:27:57,121
Mr Chow, our Far Eastern representative.
Mr Scallini.

891
01:27:57,208 --> 01:28:00,659
- It is an honour to meet you.
- You remember Mr Algo, of course.

892
01:28:00,753 --> 01:28:03,375
Shall we go? After you launch the boat,

893
01:28:03,464 --> 01:28:06,252
we'll go to the office
and sign the ownership papers.

894
01:28:06,342 --> 01:28:10,803
- Everything legal and above board.
- Above the board, yes. Good.

895
01:28:10,889 --> 01:28:14,721
- Where is it? You know...
- Well, l understood you were told.

896
01:28:14,810 --> 01:28:19,021
No, l was told, but checking, you know...

897
01:28:20,274 --> 01:28:24,022
- In the keel.
- Oh, the old keel ploy.

898
01:28:25,070 --> 01:28:28,107
All you have to do is sail
around the Caribbean for a while,

899
01:28:28,199 --> 01:28:32,777
haul her out of the water, take the
midsection out of the keel, and voilà.

900
01:28:32,870 --> 01:28:37,283
40 kilos of the finest merchandise
your experts have ever tested.

901
01:28:37,375 --> 01:28:40,993
I tell ya, it better had be
the best merchandise,

902
01:28:41,087 --> 01:28:44,124
cos my experts
certainly have tested some.

903
01:28:44,215 --> 01:28:48,083
- We have faith in our merchandise.
- That's good enough for me.

904
01:28:48,178 --> 01:28:53,136
- Now, would you like to launch her?
- l would be delighted, you know.

905
01:29:02,401 --> 01:29:04,477
<i>(coughs and sneezes)</i>

906
01:29:10,660 --> 01:29:15,203
September. A good month for the vintage.

907
01:29:15,290 --> 01:29:17,164
Well...

908
01:29:18,209 --> 01:29:20,286
Congratulations!

909
01:29:23,215 --> 01:29:24,958
Aaaargh!

910
01:29:35,227 --> 01:29:37,801
He must be a cop! Get him! Get him!

911
01:29:38,940 --> 01:29:41,016
Hey, boss!

912
01:29:50,118 --> 01:29:52,691
Look out, you Oriental idiot!

913
01:29:56,374 --> 01:29:57,917
What are you doing?!

914
01:31:01,568 --> 01:31:03,940
<i>(Marchione) Jesus Christ!</i>

915
01:31:22,965 --> 01:31:26,132
- It’s me!
- I know!

916
01:31:39,441 --> 01:31:41,517
Wait!

917
01:31:48,200 --> 01:31:50,276
<i>(gunshot)</i>

918
01:32:03,674 --> 01:32:06,213
<i>- (gunshot)
- Hey! Cancel the artillery!</i>

919
01:32:06,302 --> 01:32:08,378
<i>(gunshots)</i>

920
01:32:13,476 --> 01:32:16,893
I don't care! I don't care!
Get out of my way!

921
01:32:16,980 --> 01:32:20,563
- Hey, Al! Where are ya?
- How do I know?

922
01:32:21,777 --> 01:32:25,561
Well, wherever you are,
this is Chief Inspector Clouseau,

923
01:32:25,656 --> 01:32:28,408
and I am warning you
that if you are not careful,

924
01:32:28,492 --> 01:32:31,659
I will arrest you all in the name of the Ieu!

925
01:32:37,168 --> 01:32:38,746
You and your bright ideas.

926
01:32:38,836 --> 01:32:41,244
Let me get my hands on you.

927
01:32:41,798 --> 01:32:43,625
<i>(Dreyfus) Clouseau?</i>

928
01:32:43,716 --> 01:32:45,709
Yes?

929
01:32:45,802 --> 01:32:48,637
- Are you wounded?
- No!

930
01:32:48,722 --> 01:32:51,925
Fortunately l was saved by the darkness.

931
01:32:52,017 --> 01:32:54,590
So what we need is more light.

932
01:33:00,901 --> 01:33:04,946
Look what you did to my shoes!
Oh, I’ll kill you!

933
01:33:36,855 --> 01:33:39,144
Hello, Philippe.

934
01:33:39,233 --> 01:33:40,312
Simone!

935
01:33:40,401 --> 01:33:44,102
- What are you doing here?
- Waiting for the firecrackers to go off.

936
01:33:44,196 --> 01:33:47,696
- What firecrackers?
- The ones l just stuck in your pants.

937
01:33:47,784 --> 01:33:49,242
<i>(bang)</i>

938
01:34:29,327 --> 01:34:31,403
<i>(drum tattoo)</i>

939
01:34:52,393 --> 01:34:54,469
<i>( rousing march)</i>

940
01:36:18,024 --> 01:36:21,358
- Hello! I’m so sorry I’m late.
- i was a little worried.

941
01:36:21,445 --> 01:36:26,107
I had some rather important
police business to attend to.

942
01:36:26,200 --> 01:36:28,773
- And everything's all right?
- Absolutely fine.

943
01:36:28,869 --> 01:36:31,277
Allow me to let you in the car.

944
01:36:31,372 --> 01:36:34,123
- Please.
- It’s beautiful.

